5< /rating>
< text>
Amazing place to visit if you have connections! Gorgeous scenery, and it has some nice hiking trails. There isn't a lot of Star Wars memorabilia lying about as one would assume, most of that is all stored away. The library inside of the Main House is INCREDIBLE with an all handmade stain glassed dome. Definitely no pictures can be taken inside any of the buildings (few exceptions) and no dogs allowed either.< /text>

We retained his services to put together our Living Trust and Wills(powers-of-attorney, health directives) and completed all the paperwork within a few days, Amazing! Joshwa helped us build the trust package that fit our family, giving us the peace of mind that our children would be better prepared if something were to happen to us.

<Rating>5< /Rating><text>My air conditioning went out one hot night in June 2019 and I managed to sleep using an oscillating floor fan blowing on the bed all night.

I checked Yelp for potential repair companies where I always look for multiple good reviews. Air Repair was rather far down the list of companies, but there were numerous great reviews and I was worried about finding someone to provide service because we were in the midst of a heat wave.

I checked Air Repair’s website and I really liked the back story of the company’s origin from one guy working out of his truck to a company of four HVAC techs actually dedicated to service....which is more and more difficult to find.

I called around 9 a.m. and was greeted by Melissa who was friendly and helpful. She assigned me an appointment between 1 and 3 and sent a text to confirm with a photo of the tech who would be arriving. I received an update call when Adrian was en route to my house.

Adrian arrived within the window I was given and I recognized him and the Air Repair truck pictured on their website. He went straight to work and within minutes diagnosed a faulty motor. He quoted me a price for replacement with a 10% senior discount, but more fortunate than ever was the fact that he had the needed part in his truck.

Following installation, cold air was surging through the house again. After answering a myriad of questions for me, an invoice was emailed, I wrote a check, and Adrian was out the door and I was back in business for summer survival.

I will ALWAYS call Air Repair if I need furnace or air conditioning service.

Need I add, I received a follow up call the next day to see if everything was functional and I haven’t seen service like this since the good ole days.<//text>< pictures>
None< /pictures>

< Text>
On 8/7/2019 @ about 1:32 o'clock PM I called for service and at about @2:45 O'clock PM, a service technician (Chris) from Air Repair Heating & Air Conditioning, Victorville, CA showed up and diagnosed my dead Air Conditioning and Heating System that is over 28 years old as needing a replacement. The replacement installation was scheduled for 8/15/2019. Two service technician arrived on time and thoroughly removed the old system and installed the replacement new system (3.0 Ton 14seer RUUD Split System). During the installation process the drain line was check making sure there was no obstruction and all the lines including the brass line to the Condenser (Outdoor Unit) were still in good condition. A new electrical hook up (fuse box ) was installed. The hook up of the Outdoor Unit (Condenser) were done very neat and secured.  All the hook up inside the house for the coil and furnace were done clean and neat. A new Controller was also installed. The System was run and checked thoroughly before the Service Technician departed. Five days later, the  A/C Unit is running well. One of the installers processed the Warranty registration in the company's computer. I will proudly recommend this company for anyone's service needs. Review was done on 8/20/2019.</Text>

I had an appointment scheduled for a service call for someone to be at my house between the hours of 10am-12pm, a 2 hour window. I informed the rep who took the appointment that I started work at 130, she said she would make sure she put that in the notes.  Its was 12pm with no call and no show.. they called me at 2pm to say that someone was on their way, at 2pm!... they apologized and said they got caught up on another job.  I can understand that,  but the professional thing to do would be to call me by 12pm to let me know that, not at 2pm.

***After my review I was contacted by Chris Miller the service manager who apologized and offered to make things right by scheduling another appointment and also offering discounts on services.  I appreciated that he did that,  and would have taken him up on the offer if my husband had not already found a fix to our AC unit.  So I give it 3 stars for the effort, but I can't comment on the actual service</Text>

< text>
Dr. Friedlander has taken such good care of me through a flawless double mastectomy and hernia repair surgery. She explained everything in advance and while I came in with a  page of questions, by the time she was finished going over the surgeries, there were no questions left unanswered. The hernia was a surprise and it prevented me from having breast  reconstruction at the same time as the mastectomy.  Dr. Friedlander said she could do the hernia repair at the same time as the mastectomy, thus eliminating an extra surgery. Her office quickly scheduled the surgery so the cancer could be dealt with, which I really appreciated. Dr. Friedlander referred me to a great plastic surgeon and I have been pleased with that referral as well. If you have breast cancer,  you owe it to yourself to meet Dr. Friedlander.

I have to include her great staff who called an hour before my appointment to tell me she was running late and I could get a coffee before checking in 30 minutes later than my scheduled time.  Have you ever had a doctor's office call you to say they are running late?!! Kudos to Dr. Friedlander for creating a culture of truly caring for her patients.<//text>

< review>
I asked a cooking instructor who specializes in Vietnamese food for a recommendation for authentic Vietnamese food in Oakland. Rang Dong was among her top two picks! We've been twice. I ordered Pho the first time and the Tomato Soup the second time. Both soups were excellent! My friend had a clay pot dish with seafood and fish. He also enjoyed his meal very much. The portions are very generous and the staff are extremely friendly. They say "thank you" a lot!<//review>

< review>
My favorite spot so far in the East Bay! It's a casual, no-frills place with a simple menu focused around Pho and vermicelli dishes. Might be too plain for others but I love it. They even have garlic and chillies dipped in vinegar -- which I have not seen ANYWHERE in the States. PSA: try putting that vinegar sauce + garlic and chillies in your pho next time instead of Sriracha. Anyway, lovely spot and I'll be coming back!<//review>

< user>
113770411529025960850<//user>
<user_name>Seng Saeliew</user_name>< time>
1554681438609< /time>
<Rating>3</Rating>< review>
This location has change name and venue over the years that I've been around. The newer more modern version of this joint has a more welcoming vibe to it. The menu here are typically what you would find in many Vietnamese restaurants and this one is no different. The quality of their dish varies throughout the day and or weekend. Let me clarify this by saying that they get a certain amount of noodles on hand per day. Of course the freshest ingredients will always generally be serve during the morning to lunch and after that...it makes no business sense to make fresh batch of ingredients especially if you're going to hold them overnight. Which of course is typical but the result of this affects the outcome of its quality and your taste bud. If you're planning on dropping by in the afternoons and it looks dead, then I recommend you walk a few more blocks over to the other Pho restaurant located next door to Lucky! The high turnover rate means there is usually a fresh batch on hand. The location is convenient for many as its next to the bus stop and only minutes away from the lake where you can stretch out after your meal. If it's sunny outside and the two tables are empty then I really recommend you eat outside to catch some of the fresh air and breeze. The inside can be warmer and stuffy at times than the outside.<//review>

<review>Better than Tasty Pho. Minor changes and workers. Instead of limited menu its now revised with more coverage than just pho. Before it was run by a rather young group around early 30s now it's run by three older relatives in their 60s showing serious experience from their days. Sat outdoor in warm weather to enjoy pho is something else I tell you. They gave me a large bowl and charge me half price because when you're in the know people know too. #1 combo pho is delicious and tasty broth a little msg not enough to make me headache yet. It smell good and was really fresh that basil and mint leaves didn't show browning. Salted plum drink with lemon soda is the new vietnamese version of sprite. I suggest anyone with pho craving to try this place before another name change. Joy oy!< /review>< Name>

<user_name>Neville</user_name><Date>1540395021940</Date><Rating>5</Rating><Text>This spot was previously called Pho King or something or other, which had good food but looked pretty run down. This place has done a lot of remodel work and has upgraded the look and feel inside and out.

I got the grilled chicken rice plate, and like the prior restaurant, came with a small bowl of chicken pho broth, which scored points for me immediately. The menu is simple and has the standard options of pho, bun, salads and rice/meat combos plates. Everything was really fresh and quality. The rice plate was light, but a decent sized lunch. It came with marinated grilled chicken, a cup of white rice, and pickled cabbage and carrots.

The staff, who i assume were the owners, were really sweet and friendly. The place was short staffed the day and still got my food out in 10 munutes.

All around quality spot that I will definitely be back to.</Text><Pics>None< /Pics><Response>None<//Response><GmapID>0x808f875840dd0f89:0x5eb3625a06e64b64< /GmapID></record></dataset><record>

< user_id>
105987873160638620799</user_id>
< name>
Evan J<//name>
< Date>
1443356561585</Date>
< rate>
4<//rate>
<text>Three and a half, not 4.  Bottom line, depending on your needs, it might work for you, it might not.  Been a member going on 4 years and it works for me.  When not traveling, I'm typically there 3 to 4 days a week.  I am there primarily to swim and that works for me.  One of the best workout pools I've ever used, I wish I could take it with me when I travel haha!  Very few health clubs, let alone resorts or high end hotels offer a 50m olympic sized swimming pool and this one is ozone (salt) filtered which means I'm not sneezing and smelling of chlorine after a workout.  The hot tub is one of the best anywhere because it can hold a lot of people, the jets are like fire hoses and it is actually hot.  Both pool and hot tub do tend to pick up a lot of sand/dirt from the winds and tend to be very crowded during peak hours. The membership is far cheaper than an HOA much less owning pool so there you have it.  I'm happy.

Kennedy also does have a lot of things most gyms don't such as (again) an actual olympic sized swimming pool, full indoor basketball court, squash courts, an expansive beer/wine bar lounge area, a day care facility and lots of private rooms for events and classes.  They're also real community oriented supporting lots of local business and often having events.

What's interesting is their allocation of space in the upstairs (cardio/weight area) -- an area most health clubs have covered well, seems cramped for the overall size of the facility.  I used to use it, now I just swim.  I've toured western village in Santa Maria and their space allocation + quality and frequency of equipment has Kennedy beat several times over BUT a 60-mile round trip is out of the question and they don't have a pool half as good as Kennedy.  So depending on what you want, Kennedy might be your deal.  If you're looking for a good cardio/weight/machine gym, there might be better ones out there.< /text>< Pictures>
None</Pictures>
<resp>None< /resp>< Gmap_id>
0x80ecf0d4efa0e21f:0x6d67dd8376cf3d5a</Gmap_id>
</record></dataset><record>

2) Knowledgeable  for AC's details

<user>114348519798271758680</user><name>Irish Mckenly<//name><time>1608204708391</time><rating>4</rating>< text>
I can't remember the last time I had Kentucky fried chicken.  Pops and I stopped in for a bite after another long day. My first impression after looking at the overall review status was.... hmmm maybe we should go someplace else. But alas we were in the driveway so what the heck. My second impression after stepping in was..... wow very nice place inside. All new and up to date with all the amenities. The inside was also well kept. The menu board was nice and easy to navigate. The lady behind the counter was super sweet. I ordered the spicy "2 small chicken sammy deal ( comes with a drink, thick potato wedges "so good" a 2 slightly bigger than slider Sammy's with pickles.
Everything was very good. I deducted 1 star cuz our table could have been a little cleaner (being super picky) other wise, in my opinion (in the fast food category) this place is solidly into the 4 star area. I am really not sure why the low star count by other Yelpers. All I got to say is if you guys reviewed them on what I experienced today, you are way off the mark. Overall for fast food... good service, good food and a clean establishment.<//text>

So I use to live in Tennessee, where it is known as old country buffet. I grew up on this place and their food, nothing but great nostalgia. What happened to their quality of food? <user_id>100740809016520677814<//user_id><Pics>None</Pics>< Response>
None<//Response>
<time>1416938746022< /time><name>Rob B<//name><GmapID>0x80851427906335a5:0x198fbf17ada26692<//GmapID>< Text>
The staff is top notch friendly & helpful but the corporate office does not support the restaurant.  There is poor food planning.  On weekends they will run out of certain food products including the meat & poultry.  The bowl of new salad mix that was recently introduced is frequently empty.    The soup bar is not filled regularly & soup plates are not always available.  Many times you have to wait to collect your meal items because there are not enough plates, cups & utensils on hand at peak meal hours.  It appears the equipment is in disrepair as staff claims the dishwasher can not handle demand & the ice cream machine is malfunctioning.   Most of the time the ice cream machine is a dirty mess.   The beverage bar is out of ice & cups more times than acceptable.   The restaurant could use a makeover.  The lighting in dining area needs to be modernized.  The ceiling needs to be cleaned & brightened.  The open ceiling tiles need to be closed to keep the dirt & dust from circulating through the sub-ceiling into the dining area.  The walls need to be repainted a brighter color to make the place feel friendly & modern.   Some of the wall pictures need to be removed & updated.  This is not Horn & Hardart or Howard Johnsons.  In the warm months the management needs to do a better job keeping the mosquitoes out of the restaurant.  They hang at the front window area all day.  There is no bug control here. This restaurant's operation brings the chains reputation down & keeps away potential patrons.   If it wasn't for the reasonable prices & the frequent discounts offered most people would boycott this location.   The Bakersfield, CA  location is a model restaurant they should try to copy here.< /Text>

<rate>4< /rate>< review>
Great discount for active/retired/veteran military personnel on Monday nights! Most discount coupons are are trivial at best, except Thursday nights kids eat for $1.99 with a paying adult (limit two kids per paying adult).  On-line page depicts meatballs with spaghetti, but I have never seen meatballs with the spaghetti!  Beverage option with a meal are pricey!  When it was JJ North's, beverages were included with your meal.  I also liked JJ North's pocket menus!  When a beverage, or milk runs out, they are slow to adress it, if at all.  Usually a decent selection of food.<//review>
